latestPosts.caption:
Throughout high school, I was constantly criticised for “recording everything.” It made me question myself, like maybe I was doing too much, or not living in the moment the right way😵‍💫

For a really long time, I stopped truly being who I am, afraid that what I wanted and who I was is seen as “not normal”

But the truth is, these moments? They’re for me. To reflect. To re-live. To reminisce. To romanticise. 

and no one gets to take that away from me.

Don’t let anyone shame you for documenting your life.
This is your story. Your journey. Your memories.

And you deserve to remember them the way you want to.
